# Security Rules

Full detail: `.claude/rules/security.md` + `.claude/rules/security-rules.md`.

## Auth
- JWT lives in an **httpOnly cookie only** — never localStorage/sessionStorage/React state. `withCredentials: true` on all requests; 401 interceptor clears cache + redirects to `/login`.
- `AuthContext` is the only source of truth for the user. Frontend role checks gate UI; the **backend must always re-validate** (`@PreAuthorize`). Never trust the client alone.

## Secrets
- `VITE_`-prefixed vars are PUBLIC (bundled) — only `VITE_API_URL`, never keys/passwords.
- Backend secrets (`MONGODB_URI`, `JWT_SECRET`, `CORS_ALLOWED_ORIGINS`, `SPRING_REDIS_URL`) live in Render env, never in code.
- Never read, edit, or commit: `**/.env*`, `**/application-local.properties`, `CLAUDE.local.md`, `**/*.pem`, `**/*.key`, `**/secrets.json`.

## CORS & data
- Allowed origins from `CORS_ALLOWED_ORIGINS` env only; never `allowedOrigins("*")` in prod.
- Never return `password`; never return `email` in public/list responses. Guests shown as `Guest#XXXX`.
- No `dangerouslySetInnerHTML`. The live code preview iframe (`sandbox="allow-scripts allow-same-origin"`) is intentional — don't replicate that sandbox elsewhere.
